tempo co jakarta  president joko jokowi widodo on thursday paid a visit to three subregions located at cianjur west java which is the region most affected by monday s magnitude earthquake one of his visits was to the sukamaju state elementary school which had been shifted to a temporary relief operation site the president was accompanied by a number of officials mister of pmk muhadjir effendy mister of social affairs tri rismaharini mister of pupr basuki hadimuljono and head of bnpb suharyanto his entourage also distributed food gloves clothes childrens toys and other crucial assistance jokowi also guaranteed that renovations to houses and facilities destroyed in the earthquake will be covered by the government there will be a number of assistance programs that will see renovations enacted by the public works and housing ministry there will be some assisted by the national armed forces and there will be other independent sources said jokowi at the site mirza bagaskaraclick here to get the latest news updates from tempo on google news

tempo co jakarta  president joko jokowi widodo on thursday asserts that the government s main priority following the devastating earthquake that hit cianjur in west java is to evacuate the number of victims who are believed to still be beneath the rubbles the president said that there are still a large number of victims that have yet to be evacuated due to the difficult terrain and scattered in a broad area in a village in mangunkerta village cugenang district there are still victims who have not been evacuated from the ruins of the building so the main priority is evacuation said jokowi at the mangunkerta disaster site cugenang thursday november in terms of the distribution of logistics to survivors who are currently at refugee camps he said have been distributed as evenly as possible it includes clean water the distribution has been well i am present again at cianjur to make sure everything is going according to plan said the president the president visited a number of villages that were greatly affected by the earthquake and continued to pay visits to injured survivors at the sayang cianjur general hospital to date hundreds of people were injured and people lost their lives after a magnitude earthquake violently shook cianjur regency on monday november which was deemed a shallow quake believed to be triggered by the cimandiri fault deden abdul azizclick here to get the latest news updates from tempo on google news

tempo co jakarta  russian president vladimir putin has expressed condolences to indonesia after a powerful earthquake that struck the cianjur regency of west java yesterday putin sent his message of condolences to president joko widodo via the russian embassy on tuesday please accept my deepest condolences on the lives lost and great damages caused by the earthquake in west java province putin said in a statement released by the embassy of the russian federation in the republic of indonesia tuesday november a magnitude earthquake centered in cianjur regency shook the area on monday noon november the strong shallow land quake was felt all the way in jakarta some kilometers from the epicenter at the time of this publication the disaster is reported to have taken at least lives and injured hundreds more and displaced over people in his condolence message putin extended his heartfelt sympathy and support to the families and relatives of the deceased he also expressed his wishes for a speedy recovery to everyone affected by this disaster daniel ahmadclick here to get the latest news updates from tempo on google news

tempo co jakarta  the prime mister of singapore lee hsien loong on tuesday has written to indonesian president joko widodo to deliver his condolences on the earthquake that took place in cianjur yesterday the disaster has taken the lives of at least people most of whom are children indonesian authorities have also reported that the magnitude earthquake heavily injured more than people while at least suffered minor to moderate injuries in his letter pm lee said he was deeply saddened to hear about the loss of many lives caused by the earthquake on behalf of the government of singapore i express my deepest condolences and sympathies to the families of the victims and those affected by the disaster our thoughts and prayers are with the government and people of indonesia during this difficult time he wrote the prime mister also wrote that he is confident indonesia will overcome this adversity and recover quickly and that he would like president jokowi to let him know if singapore can be of any assistance in the relief efforts it its official website the singaporean embassy in jakarta said that it stays in close contact with indonesian authorities on the situation and will continue to monitor the developments closely there are currently no reports of singaporeans among the casualties or injured tempo coclick here to get the latest news updates from tempo on google news

tempo co cianjur  president joko jokowi widodo today november visited the cugenang road in cianjur regency which was severely hit by landslides following the cianjur earthquake west java the visit was aimed at monitoring the road repairs carried out by the ministry of public works and housing accompanied by west java governor ridwan kamil and army chief of staff kasad dudung abdurrahman during the visit the state head demanded public works and housing mister rebuild the houses of affected residents with earthquakeresistant foundations i ask the mister to repair heavily moderately and lightly damaged houses based on antiseismic standards said jokowi in cianjur on tuesday november he also asked the access to the main road to be opened so that people s mobility can run normally the national road of cugenang has been cleared today after it was filled with landslide materials however it was offlimits to the public and only emergency vehicles were allowed to pass as the cleaning was still afoot it s been open since around a m this morning starting at a m vehicles can pass it but its restricted for the public only emergency vehicles are allowed to pass the public works and housing ministry official wilan oktavian said of the cianjur earthquakeaffected road to tempo on tuesday mirza bagaskaraclick here to get the latest news updates from tempo on google news

tempo co jakarta  the press council wrote to president joko jokowi widodo on november asking for the enactment of the criminal code bill rkuhp to be postponed as it contains articles that hinder press freedom the contents of the rkuhp still limit press freedom and have the potential to criminalize journalistic work said the acting chairperson of the press council muhamad agung dharmajaya in an official statement sunday november the press council had submitted proposals to revise crucial articles to the government since july however the government in its response last october through the ministry of law and human rights had not yet accommodated it furthermore there was no explanation from the government about which articles have been accommodated and which articles have not been accommodated in addition the government did not provide any argument concerning the articles agung also stated that the press council had submitted a request to revise the draft bill to the house of representatives dpr legal commission at a public hearing on august the dpr also welcomed the request and then forwarded it to the government other than postponing the bill ratification the press council suggested case simulations on several articles that have the potential to impede press freedom and called for transparency related to the draft bill sent to the dpr so that it could be easily accessed by the people agung however continued to underline that the press council will continue to support efforts to reform the criminal code as outlined in the rkuhp academic text despite the protests discussions on the rkuhp will continue the dprs legal commission along with the ministry of law and human rights will discuss the final draft of the bill on thursday november the spokesperson for the bill socialization team albert aries stated that the draft would continue to be finalized in discussions with the dpr later any input and suggestions from civil society will certainly always be heard right to be heard and considered right to be accommodated by the government and the dpr as a form of meaningful participation albert said concerning the criminal code draft bill to tempo on monday november fajar pebriantoclick here to get the latest news updates from tempo in google news

tempo co jakarta  president joko jokowi widodo in an event held in solo central java encouraged future presidential and vice presidential candidates to avert from politicizing religion in the presidential election his message was firm as widodo said do not politicize religion we have gone through that and was dragged on too long the president spoke at the national conference of the indonesian young entrepreneurs association hipmi on november apart from urging politicians to separate religion from politics he also encouraged against the use of politics that derive from religious ethnic and race sara issues don t it will be very dangerous for a country as big as indonesia which is very diverse said jokowi he then encouraged politicians to go back to their roots that argue ideas instead of using superficial aspects to sway voters jokowi conveyed this in response to the current global situation which is currently far from being normal he reiterated his statement which had been conveyed several times that currently there are countries that have become patients of the international monetary fund or imf amidst a vulnerable global situation the president urged presidential candidates to contribute in maintaining indonesias political atmospherefajar pebriantoclick here to get the latest news updates from tempo on google news

tempo co jakarta  the indonesian government hoped that the spirit of cooperation in the series of meetings of the indonesian presidency can continue at the asia pacific economic cooperation apec summit in bangkok thailand apec must be part of efforts to accelerate economic recovery in the asia and pacific region said president jokowi in his introductory speech during a bilateral meeting with new zealand prime mister jacinda ardern in bangkok thailand on friday november in a statement from the press media and information bureau of the presidential secretariat received in jakarta on friday jokowi discussed three main issues with ardern namely strengthening economic cooperation collaboration in energy transition and strengthening cooperation in the pacific region we need to encourage market access for trade between the two countries indonesia and new zealand especially in agricultural commodities minerals iron and steel and plastics as well as cooperation in agriculture and halal certification jokowi said in the field of energy transition cooperation jokowi said indonesia continues to strengthen energy transition efforts using new and renewable energy i invite new zealand businesses to invest in developing geothermal energy in indonesia he added meanwhile in the field of regional cooperation indonesia is committed to promoting development cooperation in the pacific region therefore in indonesia will encourage the attachment of pacific countries to the association of southeast asi nations asean i want new zealand to be able to become a bridge connecting the partnership between asean and the pacific in the indopacific region jokowi said meanwhile ardern expressed her appreciation to indonesia for holding the presidency and congratulated indonesia on its asean in becoming the chairman new zealand is ready to support indonesias chairmanship in asean next year said ardern antara l imaji lasahidoclick here to get the latest news updates from tempo in google news

tempo co jakarta  during the th asiapacific economic cooperation apec summit in bangkok thailand president joko jokowi widodo reminded the challenges of the global crisis to the threat of a recession which is expected to occur soon during the summit jokowi encouraged apec economic leaders to strengthen their cooperation jokowi delivered this statement during the first session of the leaders meeting at the apec summit in the short term collaboration is necessary to overcome inflation and ensure food security jokowi said in his statement on friday november at the conference jokowi pushed for the materialization of the apec food security roadmap towards to ensure food security through several things namely innovative technology and digitization increased productivity and efficiency of the food system as well as inclusive and sustainable policies the availability of fertilizer and animal feed also needs attention to prevent a food crisis from impacting more than three billion people said president jokowi in the long term jokowi encourages the strengthening of the digital economy and green economy partnerships according to jokowi the digital economy and digital transformation are important for an inclusive economic recovery furthermore jokowi said that the digital economy such as telemedicine food delivery services digital payments and the involvement of msmes in the marketplace was very useful during the covid pandemic we must build a friendly digital economy ecosystem for msmes and startups especially through strengthening skills and digital literacy jokowi said also during the summit jokowi pushed for a green economy for regional economic recovery jokowis reasons for firmly supporting the green economy is the potential future for the regions economy and more than us billion has been used to build various green projects in apec for that i welcome thailands initiative the bangkok goals for the biocirculargreen economy this initiative will open up access to financing technology innovation and capacity building said jokowi m julnis firmansyahclick here to get the latest news updates from tempo in google news

tempo co jakarta  president joko jokowi widodo met with new zealand prime mister jacinda ardern on the sideline of the th apec summit held in bangkok on friday november according to a written statement from the presidential palace the two leaders talked about strengthening cooperation in the economy energy transition and strengthening asiapacific ties we need to encourage market access for trade between the two countries especially in agricultural commodities minerals iron and steel and plastics as well as cooperation in agriculture and halal certification jokowi said in his statement on friday november in terms of regional cooperation the president said that indonesia is committed to promoting development cooperation in the pacific and due to this reason indonesia will encourage engagement between pacific countries and asean in president jokowi conveyed indonesias commitment to continuing to strengthen its energy transition efforts using new and renewable energy and also invited new zealand business people to invest in the development of geothermal energy in indonesia jokowi hopes that new zealand can become a bridge connecting the partnership between asean and the pacific in the indopacific region prime mister jacinda expressed her appreciation for the summit that was hosted by indonesia and congratulated indonesia on chairing asean for she also said new zealand is ready to support indonesias chairmanship m julnis firmansyahclick here to get the latest news updates from tempo in google news

tempo co jakarta  president joko jokowi widodo started the th asiapacific economic cooperation or apec summit in bangkok thailand by meeting a number of other state leaders this morning he would hold a bilateral meeting with the prime mister of new zealand at the bangkok kimpton maalai hotel the president is then scheduled to attend the th apec economic leaders meeting aelm which will be held in a retreat format at the queen sirikit national convention center bangkok as read in the press release by the presidential palace friday november after meeting the world leaders jokowi would take part in the apec leaders informal dialogue with invited economic leaders outside of apec including french president emmanuel macron cambodian prime mister hun sen and saudi arabian crown prince mohammed bin salman the president will then have a bilateral meeting with the chief executive of hong kong he will then join the apec leaders lunch session read the press release in the afternoon he would hold a bilateral meeting with the crown prince of saudi arabia mohammed bin salman and then take part in the apec leaders dialogue session with abac apec business advisory council and visit the biocirculargreen bcg exhibition as a closing agenda the president would meet the king of thailand at the chakri maha prasat throne hall before returning to indonesia via suvarnabhumi international airport the president and the entourage were expected to arrive in the evening at this year s apec summit jokowi stated that indonesias main focus was pushing for an inclusive and sustainable economic recovery m julnis firmansyahclick here to get the latest news updates from tempo on google news

tempo co jakarta  indonesian president joko widodo or jokowi said hosting the summit in bal during the rainy season was quite challenging especially since the weather forecast said that rain was expected at garuda wisnu kencana gwk park i have decided that the gala dinner is at gwk the lighting is prepared well and the bmkg meteorology climatology and geophysics agency forecasted that it will rain that day said the state head when meeting journalists at apurva kempinski hotel bal on thursday november when the gala dinner was held on tuesday the gwk areas saw sunny weather many thoughts that it was because the committee hired a rain shaman no we are very scientific every time there is a cloud that raises the potential for rain the tmc team immediately tackled it he said explaining the weather modification process tmc is a weather modification technology conducted by the bmkg dwikorita karnawati the agency s head explained that tmc was a collaboration with the national research and innovation agency or brin and the indonesian air force with the support of the ministry of public works and housing and the coordinating ministry for maritime affairs and investment dwikorita also said that the tmc team started the work from november to november at local time using a total of tons of salt sown through flight sorties the goal is for the clouds to be dispelled immediately sent down as rain before entering the event area she explained the weather in the gwk area during the gala dinner was really fair with cool air temperatures and no rain heads of state seemed to enjoy the meal and were dazzled by spectacular art performances antaraclick here to get the latest news updates from tempo on google news

tempo co jakarta  president joko widodo or jokowi is pushing indonesia to become the host of the summer olympics he stated that the new capital city could be prepared as a candidate for the olympics on this occasion i express indonesias willingness and readiness to host the olympics in the future capital of nusantara said jokowi in a statement broadcast on the presidential secretariats youtube channel wednesday november he made the statement during the summit in bal before declaring indonesia to nominate as host president jokowi had also agreed on the important role of sport among the leaders he said that amid a global situation marked by the russian military invasion of ukraine the role of sport has become more important as the chief of the presidency i along with other leaders emphasize the important role of sport for health and that it can unite the world especially during this time he said according to jokowi several upcoming olympics both summer and winter will face challenges in achieving successful implementation the importance of political neutrality in international sporting events and the autonomy of sports organizations will be of concern the olympics that will take place soon include the paris olympics the milancortina winter olympics the los angeles olympics and the brisbane olympics then the gangwon youth winter olympics and the dakkar youth summer olympics the messages regarding the important role of sport in the world were previously delivered by president of the international olympic committee ioc thomas bach and president of the international football association federation fifa gianni infantino both attended the formal lunch of state leaders and delegates of the summit in bal on tuesday november the two of them addressed the current situation during the formal lunch event thomas bach called for world unity while gianni infantino asked russiaukraine for a ceasefire during the qatar world cup which will start on sunday tempo co nusa  indonesia s president joko jokowi widodo appreciated the launch of an integrated digital payment system between five countries in asean which he deemed one of the keys to strengthening a sustainable economy at the regional level central banks of five asean countries namely indonesia thailand singapore malaysia and the philippines launched a crossborder digital payment system ahead of bal summit asean is one step ahead of other countries in implementing crossborder payment said the president who attended bank indonesia s virtual event at grand hyatt nusa on monday november he said the interconnection of payments between countries was in line with one of the priority issues of the summit the conference of the leaders of the nations eks to issue policies that aim to accelerate digital transformation at the bilateral level he ensured that countries implement integrated digital transaction policies such as those between indonesia and thailand as well as singapore and thailand meanwhile in indonesia digital transactions have developed in recent times through the development of qris and bi fast so its time for this cooperation to be formalized in regional payment connectivity as a concrete form of implementing the roadmap for enhancing crossborder payments he remarked jokowi supported this initiative to be expanded to the global level given that the ease of access to payments will have a major impact on the economy particularly the tourism trade and msme sectors so that it pushes a stronger and inclusive economic recovery francisca christy rosanaclick here to get the latest news updates from tempo on google news

tempo co jakarta  president joko widodo jokowi via online means officially launched the pandemic fund on sunday which was successfully formulated by the finance and health ministers under the indonesian presidency this year the pandemic fund is a global effort to improve the global health architecture particularly through a strong and reliable financing mechanism so that in the future the world could better prevent and cope with pandemics he said i express my gratitude for countries contributions to the pandemic fund and by saying in the name of god i am launching the pandemic fund today he said at the launch two days prior to the summit on november to jokowi commended member countries and non member countries as well as philanthropic institutions that have expressed their commitment to contribute to the pandemic fund so far it has pooled approximately us billion or around trillion from countries and three philanthropic institutions the figure likely to continue to increase since australia france and saudi arabia have also expressed their commitments to contribute to the fund however president jokowi stated that the commitment of funds raised at this time is not enough given that the world bank and the world health organizations study showed that they would need approximately us billion annually in order to better prevent the risk of pandemics in the future i thank donors from and non member countries as well as from philanthropic institutions which have contributed however the funds raised are still insufficient i expect for even greater support for this pandemic fund he said he compelled everyone to support some initiatives such as the establishment of a health emergency response coordination platform in the form of an international economic fund to support pathogen monitoring the global development of digital networks vaccine certification to facilitate international travel and the establishment of fair and just research and manufacturing centers the proposal to create pandemic fund had been initiated since the italian presidency in however it was only been successfully agreed upon and completed under indonesian presidency under its leadership the member countries agreed on both pandemic fund and its governing board which is currently chaired by the indonesian finance mister for the  period chatib basri and the rwanda health mister daniel m ngamije the pandemic fund governing board is tasked with compiling various guidelines and references as well as receiving requests for funds and selecting beneficiaries countries both members and outside of the group can apply for funding from the pandemic fund to facilitate themselves in their efforts to prevent and handle future pandemic threats antaraclick here to get the latest news updates from tempo on google news

tempo co jakarta  indonesias president joko jokowi widodo asserted during the retreat session of the st asean summit today in phnom penh cambodia that the situation in myanmar should not interfere with the blocs journey or cooperation the president delivered a very strong message that its highly important for asean to keep moving forward said indonesian foreign affairs mister retno marsudi in a press statement on the sidelines of the asean summit as reported by antara retno said the situation in myanmar and issues related to international ties were discussed during the retreat session however asean leaders were more focused on discussing myanmar issues the president conveyed his statement that indonesia is extremely disappointed with the deteriorating situation in myanmar and no significant progress from the implementation of the point consensus we also dont see any commitment from the myanmar military junta to implement it said retno she went on to say that jokowi also highlighted the importance of ending the use of violence in myanmar as soon as possible the president pushes asean to immediately engage with all relevant parties retno mentioned that there are decisions made by the leaders of asean member countries that will be announced by the asean chairperson i dont have the right to disclose it because i respect the asean chair there are paragraphs points and the decision is negotiated for days and in the last two days she said the decision retno emphasized must be understood as a robust message this is a warning from asean if the situation does not improve if there is no good progress in the implementation of the point consensus then it is possible for asean to execute myanmars decision antaraclick here to get the latest news updates from tempo on google news

tempo co jakarta  president joko jokowi widodo highlighted the heroic history of the first indonesian president soekarno after granting the title of national hero to five new figures at the jakarta state palace on monday november we will also take this opportunity to emphasize the history of karnos heroism that needs confirmation especially in regards to the mprs decree no mprs on the revocation of state government power from president soekarno said the president in a youtube video broadcasted by the presidential secretariat monday november it is said that the consideration of the mprs decree protects figures of the nowdefunct indonesian communist party pki in which is known as the s pki incident however the accusation has not been proven to date since soekarno had never been tried for it at present jokowi underlined that mpr decree no mpr had revoked mprs decree no mprs and therefore no further legal action is required additionally the government honors soekarno with the title of hero of the proclamation in and in the indonesian government granted the national hero title to soekarno this means soekarno is confirmed to be loyal to and did not betray the nation and the state which are the requirement for the title president jokowi added according to jokowi the two titles further strengthen the states recognition and respect for karnos loyalty and services this is a rebuttal to the accusation that soekarno protected the pki guntur soekarnoputra who was present at the awarding ceremony event expressed gratitude for the presidents statement which confirmed that his father was not a pki member jokowis statement clears soekarnos name that he is not involved in the s pki so it is clear that soekarno is not a pki not a communist but he is a perfect nationalist and patriot said guntur m julnis firmansyahclick here to get the latest news updates from tempo on google news

tempo co jakarta  constitutional law expert bivitri susanti assessed that the formation of law in the past three years of the joko widodo or jokowi s regime was dominated by the interests of oligarchs this dominance she said occurs in almost all regulations that have been issued it is clear that the process of making laws in the last three years has prioritized oligarchs said bivitri in the forum of the national association of university student executive bodies bem si entitled maju balik indonesia or indonesias reverse progress on thursday november meanwhile a researcher from the institute for development of economics and finance indef nailul huda highlighted the worsening indonesian economy in the past three years apart from covid he said the poor economic condition was also attributable to government policies that were not in favor of the people for example the policy of fuel price hikes that will surely lead to inflation and the collapse of several companies so that layoffs will inevitably occur and the number of unemployed people will continue to increase said nailul a sociopolitical analyst from the jakarta state university ubedilah badrun believed that rampant corruption cases declining quality of democracy and the production of regulations controlled by the oligarchs can trigger public protest movements he predicted that if these protests are seen as threatening the government s power then acts of authoritarianism will be unavoidable the trend of deteriorating democratic practices during the covid pandemic still lingers at that time the government arrogantly ignored public inputs for example ignoring peoples rejection of the job creation law said ubedilah ima shafiraclick here to get the latest news updates from tempo in google news

tempo co jakarta  the national peoples defending movement gnpr and the islamic brotherhood front fpi are set to hold the th demonstration of the peoples defending action akbar and the reunion of the action today november around the jakarta merdeka palace they will urge president joko widodo alias jokowi to step down muhammad alatthas the chairperson of fpi which is the rebranded group of the disbanded islamic defenders front fpi said the president was indifferent to the voices of the people who recently took to the streets he believed the government had failed he recalled that gnpr and the people had taken to the streets several times in response to various policies created by the government but all of the demands were never addressed so we think and believe that this is due to the failure of the government headed by the honorable president joko widodo in bringing peoples lives to a better path under current conditions said alatthas who is rizieq shihabs soninlaw at a press conference at warung buncit on thursday november gnpr thus urged president jokowi to resign voluntarily as a form of ethical responsibility we demand the honorable president joko widodo resign voluntarily in accordance with mpr decree number vi mpr concerning political ethics and governance he emphasized the gnpr and fpi demonstrations and the action reunion will be held on friday afternoon around the horse statue jalan medan merdeka barat police have prepared traffic diversion in the area muhsin sabilillah click here to get the latest news updates from tempo in google news

tempo co jakarta  the religion forum is taking place in nusa bal from november  ahead of the upcoming summit in a prerecorded video president joko widodo gave his opening address that includes a message to that religion can contribute in solving global issues such as stopping wars to create a peaceful world religious leaders of various religions must work together to increase the contribution of religions in solving world problems to reduce rivalry and stop wars for the sake of a peaceful world a united world and a world that works together to pass on kindness to future generations jokowi said the forum was initiated by indonesias largest muslim organization nahdlatul ulama nu together with the muslim world league mwl in the first ever religious forum summit for the the has five main agendas the first is to focus on historical pain truthtelling reconciliation and forgiveness the second is to identify and embrace noble values originating from the worlds great religions and civilizations the third is the recontextualization of outdated and problematic religious teachings fourth is to identify the values needed to develop and ensure peaceful coexistence and the fifth focus is spiritual ecology the forum was joined by participants from countries with panelists of interfaith speakers from five continents daniel ahmadclick here to get the latest news updates from tempo in google news

tempo co jakarta  president joko jokowi widodo has appointed five new national heroes from various regions in indonesia this is announced by the coordinating mister for political law and security affairs mahfud md the government will award the title of national hero to five sons of fighters of the indonesian independence mahfud said on his twitter mohmahfudmd thursday november regions and institutions may hold tahniah event to express gratefulness he added the five new national heroes are as follows dr dr hr suharto from central java he is the personal doctor of indonesia s first president soekarno suharto also founded the indonesian planned parenthoodassociation pkbi which was the pioneer of the national population and family planning board bkkbn kanjeng gusti pangeran adipati aryo kgpaa paku alam viii of yogyakarta special region diy paku alam viii is a former deputy governor of yogyakarta during his lifetime he served great services especially for indonesian independence dr r rubin natawisastra from west kalimantan during his lifetime the doctor strived to curb the rate of maternal mortality rates during childbirth which often occurred in the practice of traditional midwives dukun anak rubin graduated from stovia school tot opleiding van inlandsche artsen or bumiputra medical school and nias or nederlands indische artsen school surabaya h salahuddin bin talabuddin from north malu salahuddin was a figure who led the movement against invaders in north malu he was repeatedly detained by the dutch imprisoned and tortured in the sawahlunto prison nusakambangan to boven goel kh ahmad sanusi from west java sanusi is the founder of alittahadiyatul islamiyah aii an organization that is actively engaged in education social and economic fields at the beginning of the japanese occupation aii was disbanded ahmad sanusi later founded the indonesian muslim association puii he also served as a member of the agency for the preparatory work for indonesian independence bpupki back in according to mahfud md the title of the national heroes will be honored by president jokowi at the state palace central jakarta on monday november m julnis tempo co jakarta  president joko jokowi widodo expressed support for defense mister prabowo subianto to run in the presidential election after attending the indo defense at jiexpo mayor central jakarta wednesday november he claimed he had already given his blessing for his former rival to return to the presidential election since the beginning i have said that i support him said the president he had also given prabowo advice regarding the election we exchange ideas about how indonesia will go forward i think it s common because it s not often that i talk with menhan defense mister but too often the state head then ordered prabowo to improve the procurement of the reserve component komcad program after the financial audit agency bpk found it violated the regulation additionally he asserted that he would evaluate the performance of ministers who were disturbed by their activities to run for president this statement also answers the constitutional court s mk ruling which allows ministers to run as presidential candidates without having to resign from their position ministers must prioritize their tasks but if we see that being a presidential candidate will interfere with the ministers duties we will evaluate whether it is really necessary for them to take a very long leave or not said jokowi m julnis firmansyahclick here to get the latest news updates from tempo on google news
